        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-07-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-07-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="418"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d418">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">710.11/2535</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Secretary of State</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-08">July 8,
                            1940</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The British Ambassador called at his own request and inquired about the meaning
                    of the Monroe Doctrine statement put out at Hyde Park on Sunday morning.<note
                        n="9" xml:id="d418fn9">See Department’s telegram No. 247, July 7, 3 p.m.,
                            <ref target="#pg_389">p. 389</ref>.</note> I replied that it was not
                    intended to be a statement of policy; that my statement given to the press a day
                    or two before<note n="10" xml:id="d418fn10">Statement of July 5, Department of
                        State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, July 6, 1940, p. 3.</note> was
                    intended to be a statement of policy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>C[<hi rend="smallcaps">ordell</hi>] H[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >ull</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
